		<div id="comment_body_64809913"><p><div class="quote"><p>Why "starting over" is a bad idea [joelonsoftware.com].</p></div><p>That article was written in the year 2000 about Netscape. That is a different situation. In this particular case, Sonos released new app versions that broke/removed a lot of features from the previous version. The fundamental difference is that Sonos does not control the APIs of the ecosystem. Google and Apple control what APIs work on their phones. Sonos might be forced to rewrite if Google or Apple changes enough about the APIs.</p></div>
	</div>

